$a = random(1, 20);
$b = random(1, 20);

$ans = 2 * $PI * ($b*$a/2 + ($a**2)/4);

BEGIN_TEXT
$PAR

Electric charge is distributed over the disk $BR \( x^2 + y^2 \leq $a
 \) so that the charge density at (x,y) is \( \sigma(x,y) = $b + x^2 +
 y^2 \) coulombs per square meter.  $BR Find the total charge on the
 disk.  
$PAR

\{ ans_rule(30) \}

END_TEXT

ANS(num_cmp($ans));


